        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 4:13PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Orland Park, moving east-northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Palos Heights, Country Club Hills, Oak Forest, Oak Lawn, Merrionette
Park, Orland Hills, Posen, Tinley Park, Mount Greenwood, Robbins,
Palos Hills, Beverly, Orland Park, Worth, Crestwood, Chicago Ridge,
Hazel Crest, Alsip, Midlothian, Burbank, Evergreen Park, Palos Park,
Bridgeview, Willow Springs, and Blue Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
